text: Olivia Cîmpian (born 1 January 2001) is a Romanian-born female artistic gymnast. At the 2016 Junior European Women's Artistic Gymnastics Championships she won the bronze medal with the Romanian team. She also competed at the 2017 European Women's Artistic Gymnastics Championships for Romania. However, as of July 2017, Cimpian has expressed her desire to compete for Hungary in future international meets.A lăsat România pentru Ungaria. Una dintre cele mai promiţătoare gimnaste a ales să concureze pentru ţara vecină, la iniţiativa tatăl său, care e fost fotbalist, adevarul.ro, 29 October 2017 She eventually left for Hungary in July, and her nationality change became official in October., FIG, 4 November 2017 Since athletes won’t be eligible to compete for a country for one year after they change nationality, Cimpian will barely be eligible for selection to Hungary’s team for the 2018 world championships.
